    ProgrammingLanguage(name: "R", introducedYear: "1993", nameOfAuthor: "Robert Gentleman", countryOrigin: "Canada", imageName: "https://cdn4.iconfinder.com/data/icons/logos-and-brands/512/285_R_Project_logo-1024.png", application: "What better place to find a good definition of the language than the R Foundation’s website? According to R-Project.org, R is “… a language and environment for statistical computing and graphics.” It’s an open-source programming language often used as a data analysis and statistical software tool. " + "\n" + "R Programming language can be seen as the powerful scientific language, some can say that it is on par with Python and MATLAB. R language is mostly used in Data Analysis, Statistical inference and Machine Learning. R offers a wide variety of statistics-related libraries and provides a favorable environment for statistical computing and design. In addition, the R programming language gets used by many quantitative analysts as a programming tool since it's useful for data importing and cleaning.",locationCoordinate: CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 51.051322852911476, longitude: -86.83266484854776))
